AT2 receptor expressing cells were grown in the additional presence of 100 nM PD123,319 (AT2 antagonist).
Saturation binding studies for determination of Kd values of the ligand were done using N-terminally Europium-labeled angiotensin-II ([Eu]AngII, H—(Eu—N1)-Ahx-Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-Phe-OH; PerkinElmer, Boston, Mass.) at 8 different concentrations ranging from 0.1 nM to 30 nM.
Displacement assays for determination of pKi values of test compounds were done with [Eu]AngII at 2 nM and 11 different concentrations of drug ranging from 1 pM to 10 μM.
Nonspecific binding was determined in the presence of 10 μM unlabeled angiotensin-II.
